incidentReports.details: Missing feed data due to API connection issues - 403 errors returned by Binance WS API.
Missing data due to hitting Binance rate limits for WS connections (403 error).
Missing initial orderbook snapshots due to Cloudflare issue (suspending Tardis account), see https://status.tardis.dev/incidents/zyfn9p37nvgn.
Increased disconnections count and WS connections timeouts resulting in small data gaps.

Missing data for about 40% of currency pairs (did not affect BTCUSDT), due to race condition that manifested after Binance maintenance window and failed to recognise symbols being enabled in quick succession via API (status change from BREAK to TRADING), permanent fix has been deployed.
Missing depthSnapshot messages caused by hitting API rate limits by our proxy servers.
Missing data caused by new version deployment rolling out too slow.
Missing data due to virtual machine crash. Crash was caused by hardware issue on the physical machine hosting VM which has been automatically replaced with healthy one by auto-repair logic.
WS API was very frequently closing open connections with "EndpointUnavailable" status. It caused data gaps and delayed order book snapshots fetched from REST API due to rate limits.
API rate limits hit due to deployment bug. It caused increased disconnections count and data gaps, hotfix has been deployed.
Increased disconnections count triggering API rate limits thresholds that caused some data gaps. It has been investigated and fixed.
Intermittent Kubernetes Node network issue caused increased disconnections count and establishing connection timeouts that resulted in missing data.
Increased count of reconnections that could cause some data missing. It has been investigated and fixed - too small "stale connection" timeout.
Missing data (~8 seconds) caused by moving Binance data collection infrastructure from London to Tokyo GKE cluster.

Missing initial order book snapshot data (depthSnapshot) and occasional initial order book snapshots not overlapping with depthUpdate messages due to exceeding Binance REST API rate limits. Fix has been applied, we're closely monitoring this issue.
Missing initial order book snapshot data (depthSnapshot) and occasional initial order book snapshots not overlapping with depthUpdate messages due to exceeding Binance REST API rate limits.

Increased count of reconnections that could cause some missing data and missing book snapshots. It was caused by logic that was incorrectly detecting that there was an issue with real-time subscription. It has been investigated and fixed.
Increased count of reconnections due to deployment configuration issue that has been indentified and fixed. There could cause missing data during that time.

K8S node where recording containers are running became unresponsive (network issue, no access to or from node) and has been automatically replaced with healthy node by auto-repair logic. Unfortunately that caused missing data feed for approximately 15 minutes.
